Arsenal legend, Paul Merson has stated that he is “worried” for Liverpool following Sadio Mane’s departure. Mane opted to join Bayern Munich from Liverpool a few days ago, completing a move worth around £35 million. The Senegalese international signed a three-year deal with the Bundesliga champions. But Merson believes Liverpool could feel the effects of Mane’s absence, adding that his departure was a massive miss. When asked how Mane’s departure will affect the Reds, he replied (as quoted by the Liverpool Echo): “Massive miss, massive. “I worry for Liverpool because they have got an unbelievable manager, but people forget Mane was a big game player.”